Series in Pandas is a 1-D array, like a column in a table.
It is a labeled array that can hold data of any type.
The series() method is used for this and has following parameters:
1. data: The data to be stored in the pandas library.
2. index: The index value should have the same length as the data.
3. dtype: It is the datatype for the output series.
4. name: Set the series name with the name parameters.
5. copy: To copy the input data.
It has some attributes:
1. dtype: Returns the dtype.
2. ndim: Returns the Number of dimensions.
3. size: Returns the number of elements.
4. name: Returns the name of the series.
5. hasnans: Returns True if NANs are in the series.
6. index: The index of the series.
7. head(): Returns the first n rows.
8. tail(): Returns the last n rows.
9. info(): Display the summary of the series.
